          &lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s been a while and a lot has happened in my life. Focusing on the positive I thought it might be nice to do a little recap of my trip to Vienna two weeks ago for this year&amp;rsquo;s Pelikan Hub üôÇ&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This time the event took place in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.boesner.at/unsere-standorte/wien&#34;&gt;local Boesner store&lt;/a&gt;. For those who don&amp;rsquo;t know, Boesner is a German chain for art supplies. Whenever someone I know needs something for drawing or painting, they go there, so it must be good üòâ In the store in Vienna there is also a nice caf√© which kept open for us beyond the normal business hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In there we had pretty much all the tables available to us. While some folks came with huge collections of Pelikan pens, pretty much everyone also had fountain pens from a wide range of other makers, from large to small. Thanks to that I could finally try if a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.pilotpen.de/Capless-Decimo/1049003F&#34;&gt;Pilot Capless Decimo&lt;/a&gt; really fit into my Plotter&amp;rsquo;s pen holder. I guess, I really need to eventually get one üòÖ&lt;/p&gt;
