      <title>Ninebot F3 after 50km</title>
      
      <link>https://zerokspot.com/weblog/2025/09/09/ninebot-f3-after-50km/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 14:34:19 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/weblog/2025/09/09/ninebot-f3-after-50km/</guid>
      <description>
          &lt;p&gt;Over the last week or so I‚Äôve managed drive around 50km with my new &lt;a href=&#34;https://uk-en.segway.com/products/f3-e&#34;&gt;Segway/Ninebot F3 E&lt;/a&gt; and I think it‚Äôs time for a quick review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In general, I‚Äôm very happy with the scooter. It is stable and has a solid feel to it which is especially handy when a road isn‚Äôt as smooth as it should be. I also did some driving in the night and the front light is powerful enough to light up half a road. Perfect for streets that have no lights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the negative side, it is heavier than anticipated. The scooter is still much more portable than my e-bike but I wouldn‚Äôt carry it around for more than 100m. Another issue I had was that the F3 is not intended to be held vertically. Imagine a bus where you don‚Äôt want to take too much space up and therefore want to just lean the folded scooter somewhere. It‚Äôs doable but not comfortably so due to the weight &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; the area on rear that is intended for a license plate. Could I hold it up with the rear end at the top? That‚Äôs something that I also tried and it works ‚Äúbetter‚Äù but is also uncomfortable since I have to use the steering bar to hold.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least for Austrian ‚ÄúS-Bahn‚Äù trains the scooter is also about 10cm too long to fit under the seats there. Luckily, that wasn‚Äôt really an issue so far, though.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now let‚Äôs briefly talk about the range: The device is advertised to do up to 70km on a full charge. That‚Äôs only for the Eco mode, though, which goes 15km/h. This would be fine but I doubt that it‚Äôs actually the case. I usually use the Eco, Drive (most of the time), and Sport mode depending on where I‚Äôm driving and so far I‚Äôve had to recharge twice. It‚Äôs still decent IMO and I‚Äôm happy with it but given the weight issue it‚Äôs a tiny bit disappointing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That also sums up my general opinion on my first e-scooter: It‚Äôs a solid device and I enjoy riding it. The weight is a bit of an issue but that‚Äôs about it. I‚Äôm happy with the purchase as it worked flawlessly for those scenarios I wanted to have it üôÇ&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After a week, though, I really longed for my bike üòÇ&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
